{
  "stem": "868.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I would very much appreciate a chance to be allowed to continue attending school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was impressed by that, perhaps by the guts I had to stop him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he said to one of his administrators, he said, give him a pass, him alone, and if he can come back with a guarantee that they will not be a charge to the state and that he has a place-- he and his family, has a place to live, you can let them go.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I was given this pass.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went to the nearest town which, was Montpellier, M-O-N-T-P-E double L- I-E-R, where I knew there was a French-Jewish organization.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "See, at that time they were still kind of respectful of French Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Their energy had been directed until then at foreign Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So at that time, the French Jews were still allowed to exist, sort of.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had a committee of assistance.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I went there and I explained the situation, and they provided me with a, a place where we could live, which was outside of, of town, but a place, and a guarantee that they would support us for living needs, you know, food and lodging.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Equipped with those papers, I went back to the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And amazingly, we were left-- we were let go out of the camp under the envious eyes, of course, of everybody else.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So we lived in Montpellier, and I went back to school [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] until [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Allies landed in North Africa.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "At that moment, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the Germans invaded the South of France and occupied all of France immediately.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "What was until now the Free Zone was now occupied, just like the north.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
